sba","marks":1,"options":["Hard palate only","Soft palate and majority of uvula","Hard palate and soft palate only","Soft palate, uvula and tonsillar pillars","Soft palate and base of uvula only"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Mallampati classification system has four classes based on the visibility of oropharyngeal structures during examination:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClass 1: \u003Cstrong\u003ESoft palate, uvula and tonsillar pillars\u003C/strong\u003E visible\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClass 2: \u003Cstrong\u003ESoft palate and majority of uvula\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClass 3: \u003Cstrong\u003ESoft palate and base of uvula only\u003C/strong\u003E visible\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClass 4: Only \u003Cstrong\u003Ehard palate\u003C/strong\u003E visible\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA higher Mallampati score (3 or 4) suggests a more difficult intubation due to limited visualization of posterior structures. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ehard palate and soft palate only\u003C/strong\u003E view does not correspond to any Mallampati class.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Mallampati classification assesses visibility of posterior oral structures to predict difficulty of intubation","Mallampati class 3 shows only soft palate and base of uvula visible on oral examination"],"references":["Green SM, Roback MG. Is the Mallampati Score Useful for Emergency Department Airway Management or Procedural Sedation? Ann Emerg Med. 2019 Aug;74(2):251-259. doi: 10.1016/j.annemergmed.2018.12.021. Epub 2019 Feb 16. PMID: 30782435.","Stutz EW, Rondeau B. Mallampati Score. 2023 Aug 5. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 36256766.","Naftalovich R, Oydanich M, Adeola J, Eloy JD, Rodriguez-Correa 